1.00	Pir_Sadardin	Pir Sadardin	Pir Sadardin or Pir Sadruddin was a fourteenth century Ismaili Da'i and is regarded as the founder of the Khoja Ismaili sect, also called Satpanth. Born in Persia, Sadardin later travelled to the Indian sub-continent, settled in the Sindh area, founded the Khoja community and developed the Khojki script.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/Basmala.svg/180px-Basmala.svg.png
